acy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nikomatsakis/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "open_issues": 0, "closed_issues": 66, "state": "closed", "created_at": "2018-06-29T18:51:49Z", "updated_at": "2018-12-08T10:44:16Z", "due_on": "2018-12-06T08:00:00Z", "closed_at": "2018-12-08T10:44:16Z"}, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2018-04-09T21:41:04Z", "updated_at": "2018-09-14T18:16:35Z", "closed_at": "2018-09-14T18:16:35Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "(NB. This is assuming my in-progress branch)\r\n\r\nIf you run `issue-36082.rs` in NLL mode, you get:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n> rustc --stage1 issue-36082.rs  -Zborrowck=mir\r\nerror[E0597]: borrowed value does not live long enough\r\n  --> issue-36082.rs:21:19\r\n   |\r\n21 |     let val: &_ = x.borrow().0;\r\n   |                   ^^^^^^^^^^  - temporary value only lives until here\r\n   |                   |\r\n   |                   temporary value does not live long enough\r\n...\r\n30 |     println!(\"{}\", val);\r\n   |                    --- borrow later used here\r\n```\r\n\r\nThere is no suggestion about using a let binding to increase the lifetime of the temporary, unlike AST borrowck:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n> rustc --stage1 issue-36082.rs\r\nerror[E0597]: borrowed value does not live long enough\r\n  --> issue-36082.rs:21:19\r\n   |\r\n21 |     let val: &_ = x.borrow().0;\r\n   |                   ^^^^^^^^^^  - temporary value dropped here while still borrowed\r\n   |                   |\r\n   |                   temporary value does not live long enough\r\n...\r\n31 | }\r\n   | - temporary value needs to live until here\r\n   |\r\n   = note: consider using a `let` binding to increase its lifetime\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat said, this seems like a case where the AST borrowck message could *also* be improved. I doubt many people understand it very well. ", "closed_by": {"login": "bors", "id": 3372342, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzNzIzNDI=", "avatar_ur